    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Fifty-four patients (27 women) aged 25-45 years who had presented to our faculty for
        periodontal and other dental problems and consented to participate were enrolled in the
        study.

        Group 1 - subjects with healthy periodontal status Group 2 - subjects with untreated
        gingivitis Group 3 - subjects with untreated chronic periodontitis (indicted by
        radiographic evidence of bone loss and clinical attachment loss &gt; 5 mm in more than six
        teeth)
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
